title: iOS Developer
jobDescription:
We are looking for talented iOS Developers who are passionate and know-how the process of building scalable and secure functionality on top of the iOS platform. You will be associated with a qualified and experienced pool of people with whom you will build correlations by sharing your experience and growing your capabilities.

Primary Objectives
  • Practical experience in applying OOPs techniques and design patterns in everyday
    coding.
  • Proper knowledge of Swift 5+, Xcode, iOS development life cycle
  • Basic knowledge of iOS SDK, different versions of iOS, and how to deal with different
    screen sizes.
  • Practical experience of Auto Layout.
  • Experience working with remote data via REST API and JSON.
  • Understanding of iOS App Code signing process and deployment process.
  • Ability to understand business requirements and translate them into technical
    requirements.
  • Knowledge of third-party libraries integration.
  • Should be ready to learn new things and take challenges.
Roles Responsibilities
  • Translate designs and wireframes into high-quality code.
  • Creating app updates, including bug fixes and additional features, for release.
  • Design, build and maintain high-performance, reusable, and reliable swift code.
  • Deliver high performance, scalable native application.
  • Collaborating with UI and UX Designers, as well as Software Testers, to ensure that
    each app is presentable and in perfect working order.
  • Proofreading your code and correcting mistakes before each app is released.
  • Ensure the best possible performance, quality, and responsiveness of the
    application.
  • Strictly follow instructions guidelines given by a senior developer or team leader.
  • Help maintain code quality, organization, and automatization.
  • Fully responsible for mobile app development in the team.
  • Continuously discover new ways to implement new technologies to improve
    development efficiency.
  • Work on improving application performance.
  • Help your team solve problems in a way that makes sense for iOS users and our
    codebase.
  • Upgrade the technical knowledge regularly.
Technical Skills You Should Have
  • Excellent understanding of Swift, Xcode, Core Data, Auto Layout, Git, iOS Human.
  • Interface Guidelines, REST APIs and JSON.
  • Complex problem solving and ability to multitask.
  • Top-notch teamwork and communication skills.
  • Creativity and brainstorming.
  • Unwavering curiosity.
  • Familiarity with continuous integration.
  • A systematic and quality-oriented way of working.
Key Expertise
  • Swift, Xcode, Core Data, Auto Layout, Git, iOS Human
    Interface Guidelines, REST APIs and JSON.
Qualification
  • Bachelor s Degree in Computer Science or Computer Engineering,
  • B.Tech (CSE/ IT),BCA, MCA.
Experience
  • 1 to 2 years of experience in iOS Development
